---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/main.astro";

import { m } from "../../paraglide/messages.js";
---

<MainLayout class="contentContainer">
  <article class="termsContent">
    <section class="header">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="lastUpdatedDate">Last updated: 17 July 2026</p>
    </section>

    <section class="termsBody">
      <p>Welcome to readthisshit.fyi ("RTS", "we", "our", or "us").</p>
      <p>
        RTS is a community-driven website for finding useful websites, articles, and other resources. We believe good information should be
        easy to find, and we rely on our community to help keep the directory useful and trustworthy.
      </p>
      <p>By using RTS, you agree to these Terms of Service.</p>

      <h2>1. Using RTS</h2>
      <p>You are welcome to browse RTS without creating an account.</p>
      <p>Creating an account allows you to submit websites, write reviews, create collections, and use other community features.</p>
      <p>You agree to use RTS responsibly and in accordance with these Terms, our Privacy Policy, and our Community Guidelines.</p>
      <p>If you do not agree with these Terms, please do not use RTS.</p>

      <h2>2. Accounts</h2>
      <p>You are responsible for your account and anything done through it.</p>
      <p>When creating an account, you agree to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>provide accurate information;</li>
        <li>keep your login method secure;</li>
        <li>avoid impersonating another person or organization;</li>
        <li>avoid creating accounts for spam, abuse, or ban evasion.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Authentication is currently provided through email magic links. Passwords, passkeys, two-factor authentication, and other login
        methods may be added in the future.
      </p>
      <p>We reserve the right to reclaim usernames that impersonate other people, organizations, trademarks, or the RTS team.</p>

      <h2>3. User Content</h2>
      <p>RTS allows users to contribute content such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>website suggestions;</li>
        <li>reviews;</li>
        <li>profile information;</li>
        <li>other content made available through the Service.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You keep ownership of the content you create.</p>
      <p>
        By submitting content to RTS, you give us a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free license to store, display, reproduce, and
        distribute your content only as needed to operate, maintain, improve, secure, and promote RTS.
      </p>
      <p>You are responsible for the content you submit.</p>
      <p>You confirm that you have the right to publish any content you upload.</p>
      <p>Submitting content does not guarantee that it will be published or remain available on RTS.</p>
      <p>Moderators may remove content that violates these Terms or the Community Guidelines.</p>

      <h2>4. Reviews</h2>
      <p>Reviews should help other people make informed decisions.</p>
      <p>Write reviews that are honest, constructive, and based on your own experience.</p>
      <p>Do not use reviews to harass people, spread false information, or attack individuals.</p>
      <p>Reviews reflect the opinion of their authors. They do not represent the views of RTS.</p>

      <h2>5. Website Submissions</h2>
      <p>RTS exists to help people find useful and trustworthy websites.</p>
      <p>When you suggest a website, you should make sure your submission is accurate and made in good faith.</p>
      <p>Do not submit websites that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>contain malware or harmful software;</li>
        <li>are used for phishing or scams;</li>
        <li>promote illegal activity;</li>
        <li>primarily contain explicit sexual content;</li>
        <li>exist only to advertise products or services without useful content;</li>
        <li>intentionally spread false or misleading information;</li>
        <li>violate the rights of others.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Submitting a website does not guarantee that it will be accepted.</p>
      <p>
        Every submission is reviewed before it becomes publicly available. We reserve the right to approve, reject, remove, or update any
        submission.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may edit titles, descriptions, tags, categories, or other metadata to improve accuracy and consistency. We will not change the
        meaning of user reviews.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to use RTS to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>break the law;</li>
        <li>upload or distribute malware;</li>
        <li>spam users or moderators;</li>
        <li>harass, threaten, or intimidate others;</li>
        <li>publish hate speech or discriminatory content;</li>
        <li>dox or expose personal information without permission;</li>
        <li>upload copyrighted material without permission;</li>
        <li>attempt to bypass moderation or account restrictions;</li>
        <li>interfere with the operation or security of RTS;</li>
        <li>scrape, crawl, or collect data in a way that harms the Service or bypasses reasonable rate limits.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If something is technically possible but clearly harms the community or the Service, it is still considered a violation of these
        Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Moderation</h2>
      <p>RTS is moderated by people appointed by the project owner.</p>
      <p>Moderation decisions are based on the Community Guidelines and the best interests of the community.</p>
      <p>Moderators do not edit user submissions. They either approve, reject, or remove them.</p>
      <p>We aim to make moderation decisions fairly, consistently, and in good faith.</p>
      <p>If you believe a moderation decision was incorrect, you may appeal by contacting us.</p>
      <p>We are not required to review repeated or abusive appeals about the same decision.</p>

      <h2>8. Suspension and Termination</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to suspend, restrict, or permanently terminate any account that, in our reasonable judgment, harms the
        community or the Service.
      </p>
      <p>Examples include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>repeated violations of these Terms;</li>
        <li>spam or automated abuse;</li>
        <li>ban evasion;</li>
        <li>attempts to compromise the security of RTS;</li>
        <li>illegal activity;</li>
        <li>behavior intended to disrupt the community.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Account suspension may happen without prior notice if immediate action is necessary to protect users or the Service.</p>

      <h2>9. Account Deletion</h2>
      <p>You may request deletion of your account by contacting us.</p>
      <p>When an account is deleted, personal information is anonymized where reasonably possible.</p>
      <p>
        Public website submissions remain attributed to "Deleted User." This helps preserve discussions and references while protecting your
        identity.
      </p>
      <p>Reviews written by deleted accounts are removed.</p>
      <p>
        Some technical records, backups, or security logs may remain for a limited period where necessary for security, legal compliance, or
        disaster recovery.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Copyright</h2>
      <p>Respect the intellectual property rights of others.</p>
      <p>Only submit content that you have permission to use.</p>
      <p>If you believe content on RTS infringes your copyright, contact us with enough information for us to identify the material.</p>
      <p>Every copyright complaint is reviewed by the project owner.</p>
      <p>Knowingly submitting false copyright complaints may result in action against your account.</p>

      <h2>11. Availability</h2>
      <p>We work to keep RTS available and reliable.</p>
      <p>We do not guarantee uninterrupted service.</p>
      <p>
        Maintenance, updates, hardware failures, security incidents, or circumstances outside our control may temporarily interrupt the
